Four men have been charged with murder after a man's death in Stoke-on-Trent.Thapelo Jali, 21, died shortly after he was found with serious injuries in an alleyway on Buccleuch Road, Normacot, at about 01:00 BST on Monday.Ezaan Hussain, 20, Tuheed Hussain, 23, Tayyab Hussain, 26, and Zubair Hussain, 45, all from Longton, Stoke-on-Trent, were charged with murder.They were remanded into custody after a hearing at the North Staffordshire Justice Centre on Friday and will next appear on Monday at a crown court to be determined, Staffordshire Police said.
